snippet.title: On the hunt for Google's Easter eggs
snippet.description: Here is a roundup of Google's jokes and hoaxes currently on the loose. Did you miss the Tardis?

snippet.title: Gingerbread Optimus Prime: Dessert in disguise
snippet.description: "Confectibots, roll out!" There's more than meets the eye to this tasty Transformer. But what if all food could change into powerful robots?

snippet.title: Cook up IFTTT recipes on your iPad
snippet.description: With version 2.0 of the popular iOS app, iPad users can now create and manage their if/thens. Plus: push notifications!

snippet.title: 3D-printed Nokia logo a sweet treat for Easter
snippet.description: The company creates a software rendering of its logo and then uses a 3D printer and liquid chocolate to create #Chokia.

snippet.title: Create, manage recipes with IFTTT for iPhone
snippet.description: You can now automate your digital life from your iPhone using the official IFTTT app.

snippet.title: Easter ideas: Virtual egg hunts and last-minute cards
snippet.description: Add a little tech to your Easter celebration this year. In this Tech Minute, CNET's Kara Tsubio recommends apps to send last-minute cards, keep kids guessing on a virtual egg hunt, and learn creative egg dyeing techniques.

snippet.title: The cake is the truth: Chef whips up video game recipes
snippet.description: The Gourmet Gaming blog plucks foods from video games out of their virtual worlds and offers them as real-life recipes. Think Cluckin' Bell Fowl Burger from Grand Theft Auto IV and Bioshock Finkton's Baked Beans.

snippet.title: Disney, channeling Silicon Valley, launches startup accelerator
snippet.description: Working with Techstars, the media giant is forming 10 startups with mentors like CEO Bob Iger and giving them access to Disney's IP.

snippet.title: Roku adds WatchESPN and Watch Disney channels
snippet.description: The new apps significantly bolster Roku's live TV offerings, although they require authentication from an affiliated cable TV provider.

snippet.title: DirecTV reportedly in talks with Disney for Internet deal
snippet.description: The satellite TV provider is in negotiations to offer the media giant's content as part of an Internet-based product, Reuters reports.
